- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The paper uses boolean matrices to study the properties of characteristic matrices and their application to boolean matrix decomposition, which are topics in discrete mathematics. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper's focus on approximation operators and boolean matrices has applications in artificial intelligence, particularly in the area of rough sets. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper's use of boolean matrices and their decomposition has applications in information theory, particularly in the area of coding theory.
